===Etymology===
From {{etyl|da}} ''[[isbjerg]]'' or {{Norw.}}/{{etyl|sv}} ''[[isberg]]'' both meaning ''mountain of ice''. First used to describe a glacier as seen at a distance from a ship then used as a term to describe the floating chunks of ice broken off from such glaciers.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A huge mass of ocean-floating [[ice]] which has broken off a [[glacier]] or [[ice shelf]]
#: ''The Titanic hit an '''iceberg''' and sank''.

